1
00:00:02,360 --> 00:00:04,271
So he survived. What's the worry?

2
00:00:04,360 --> 00:00:08,433
He didn't even lose a limb,
an eyeball, bladder control.

3
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:12,399
The point is listen to them.
They've lost faith in old symbols.

4
00:00:12,480 --> 00:00:15,552
They're ready to bond with you,
the icon of the future.

5
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:17,471
If it works, don't fix it.

6
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,869
We'll celebrate tonight
at my annual Max-querade Ball.

7
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:22,076
Shreck and Cobblepot...

8
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:25,438
the visionary alliance. Come on.

9
00:00:43,640 --> 00:00:45,517
<i>When it came time...</i>

10
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:49,036
<i>to ensure the safety of our fair city...</i>

11
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:51,957
<i>did the Mayor have a plan?</i>

12
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:53,029
No!

13
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:54,269
<i>No!</i>

14
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:58,120
<i>He relied on a man.</i>

15
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:00,832
<i>A Batman.</i>

16
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:05,313
<i>A ticking time-bomb</i>
<i>of a costumed freak...</i>

17
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:08,710
Our prime concern
is this ghastly grotesque.

18
00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:12,197
But let's not forget
about repairing the Batmobile.

19
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:14,396
There's security to consider.

20
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:18,075
It's not as though we can take it
to any old Joe's body shop, is it, sir?

21
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:19,554
Security?

22
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,756
Who let Vicki Vale into the Batcave?

23
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:24,070
I'm sitting there working,
and I turn around...

24
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:26,276
and there she is. "Hi, Vick. Come on in."

25
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:37,634
- Ready?
- I think I'll take the stairs.

26
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:40,388
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

27
00:01:57,720 --> 00:02:01,952
PENGUIN: <i>You ask me</i>
<i>am I up here for personal glory?</i>

28
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:04,475
<i>No.</i>

29
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:08,950
<i>I toiled for many years...</i>

30
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:14,956
<i>in utter obscurity</i>
<i>beneath your boulevards.</i>

31
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:19,911
<i>The glory that I yearn to recapture...</i>

32
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:23,273
<i>is the glory of Gotham!</i>

33
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:42,839
<i>How can this be accomplished?</i>

34
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:48,349
<i>I know you're all concerned.</i>

35
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,112
<i>Hey, just relax.</i>

36
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:56,910
<i>I'll take care of the squealing,</i>
<i>wretched, pinhead puppets of Gotham!</i>

37
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,919
I didn't say that.

38
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:10,949
<i>You gotta admit,</i>
<i>I played this stinking city...</i>

39
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:13,190
<i>like a harp from hell!</i>

40
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,391
[Crowd booing]

41
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,279
Get out of here!

42
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:14,914
Why is there always someone who
brings eggs and tomatoes to a speech?

43
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:34,068
[Looming instrumental music]

44
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:39,713
There he is!

45
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:11,073
My babies.

46
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,838
Did you miss me?

47
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:28,872
Did you miss me?

48
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:32,271
Great speech, Oswald.

49
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:37,108
My name is not Oswald! It's Penguin!

50
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,550
I am not a human being!

51
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:42,877
I am an animal! Cold-blooded!

52
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,872
Crank the AC!

53
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:47,838
Where are my lists? Bring me the names!

54
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,393
It's time.

55
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:54,314
These are the names
of the first-born sons of Gotham City.

56
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,472
Just like I was.

57
00:05:56,720 --> 00:06:00,713
And like me, a terrible fate waits for them.

58
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:04,318
Tonight, while their parents party...

59
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:07,028
they'll be dreaming away...

60
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,191
in their safe cribs...

61
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:11,351
their soft beds...

62
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,670
and we will snatch them...

63
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:15,751
carry them into the sewer...

64
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:19,992
and toss them
into a deep, dark, watery grave.

65
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,359
Penguin?

66
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:26,475
I mean, killing sleeping children,
isn't that a little...

67
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:37,998
No, it's a lot.

68
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,319
Mr. Wayne, a reminder.

69
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:53,439
Tonight is that loathsome party
hosted by the odious Mr. Shreck.

70
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:56,592
May we RSVP
in the resoundingly negative?

71
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,348
Not interested.

72
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,509
Although...

73
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,831
Selina Kyle might be there.

74
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:12,388
[Upbeat dance music playing]

75
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:30,071
Ingenious costume.

76
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,673
Let me guess.

77
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:34,149
Trust fund goodie-goodie.

78
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:36,279
Feeling good?

79
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:40,835
Well, you almost made a monster
the mayor of Gotham City.

80
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:43,150
I am the light of this city...

81
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:45,869
and I am its mean, twisted soul.

82
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,151
Does it matter who's mayor?

83
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,629
- It does to me.
- Yawn.

84
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:02,868
[SIow rhythmic music playing]

85
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,349
Hi.

86
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:30,000
I'm sorry about yesterday, but I had...

87
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:33,277
a pretty big deal come through.
Fall through, actually.

88
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:36,113
It's okay.
I had to go home and feed my cat.

89
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,350
So no hard feelings, then?

90
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:50,193
Actually...

91
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,111
semi-hard, I'd say.

92
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:03,675
There's a big, comfy California King
over in Bedding.

93
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,552
What do you say?

94
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:09,675
You mean, take off our costumes?

95
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:14,915
I guess I'm tired of wearing masks.

96
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:16,788
Me, too.

97
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,792
Let me ask you something.

98
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,797
Why'd you come tonight?

99
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:25,356
- You first.
- To see you.

100
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,874
That's lovely.

101
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:33,595
I really wish I could say the same,
but I came for Max.

102
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,832
What do you mean? You and...

103
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:39,273
Not you and Max.

104
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,233
Me and Max.

105
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:50,515
No. This and Max.

106
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:56,829
Don't give me
a killing-Max-won't-solve-anything speech.

107
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:58,069
Because it will.

108
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:01,311
Aren't you tired of this
sanctimonious robber-baron...

109
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,994
always coming out on top
when he should be six feet under?

110
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:06,435
I'm sure you have a lot of problems
with your boss...

111
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,715
but who the hell do you think you are?

112
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,590
I don't know anymore, Bruce.

113
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:29,310
A kiss under the mistletoe.

114
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:34,635
Mistletoe can be deadly if you eat it.

115
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:37,188
But a kiss can be even deadlier...

116
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,872
if you mean it.

117
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:52,073
Oh, my God.

118
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:55,394
Does this mean we have to start fighting?

119
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:57,992
Let's go outside.

120
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:21,550
[Tense instrumental music]

121
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,911
- Are you okay?
- I'm all right.

122
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:45,755
You didn't invite me, so I crashed!

123
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:52,072
- What do you want?
- Right now, my troops...

124
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:54,549
are fanning out across town...

125
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:57,438
for your children! Yes!

126
00:11:57,680 --> 00:12:00,194
For your first-born sons!

127
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:03,273
The ones you left defenseless at home...

128
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,830
so you could dress up like jerks...

129
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:08,480
get juiced and dance...

130
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:09,948
badly!

131
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,356
I've personally come...

132
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:19,189
for Gotham's favorite son:

133
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,998
Mr. Chip Shreck.

134
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:25,471
You're coming with me,
you great white dope...

135
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:28,558
to die way down in the sewer.

136
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:32,633
Not Chip. If you have an iota
of human feeling, take me instead.

137
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:36,391
I don't. So, no.

138
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:38,471
I'm the one you want. Ask yourself.

139
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:41,677
Isn't it Max Shreck
who manipulated and betrayed you?

140
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:44,069
Isn't it Max, not Chip...

141
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:47,756
who you want to see immersed
to his eyeballs in raw sewage?

142
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:54,311
Okay, you got a point.

143
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:57,198
I'll let the little prince live for now.

144
00:12:57,280 --> 00:12:58,759
In the duck!

145
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:27,110
This is gonna be good...

146
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:32,151
to cut down a whole crop
of Gotham's most promising...

147
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:34,118
before their prime.

148
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:39,078
You ask me, how do I lure them in?

149
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:45,359
A little Pied Penguin action.

150
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:50,312
And you get to watch them sink...

151
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:52,517
into a deep puddle...

152
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:55,433
of your industrial byproducts.

153
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:58,234
Then you join them.

154
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:09,990
[Eerie instrumental music]

155
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:24,677
[Baby crying]

156
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:33,798
Would you hurry up
and get those kids loaded already?

157
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:45,194
Right this way, kiddies. Come on.

158
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,872
Come with me.

159
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:04,755
So, where are all the children?

160
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,874
"Batman."

161
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,990
My dear penguins...

162
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:33,758
we stand on a great threshold.

163
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,790
It's okay to be scared.

164
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,720
Many of you won't be coming back.

165
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:43,788
Thanks to Batman, the time has come...

166
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:46,589
to punish all of God's children.

167
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:51,516
First, second, third, and fourth-born!

168
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,272
Why be biased?

169
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,510
Male and female!

170
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:58,398
Hell, the sexes are equal...

171
00:15:58,520 --> 00:16:02,832
with their erogenous zones
blown sky-high!

172
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:08,751
Forward march!

173
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:12,398
The liberation of Gotham...

174
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:14,431
has begun!

175
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,234
[Valiant instrumental music]

176
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:59,510
ALFRED: <i>The penguins</i>
<i>are moving above ground.</i>

177
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:27,595
POODLE LAD Y: <i>Penguin army</i>
<i>approaching launch destination...</i>

178
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:29,318
<i>at Gotham Plaza.</i>

179
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,309
<i>One minute until ignition.</i>

180
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,675
They wouldn't put me on a pedestal...

181
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:37,354
so I'm laying them on a slab!

182
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:41,193
<i>The penguins seem to be converging</i>
<i>on Gotham Plaza.</i>

183
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:06,357
<i>Thirty seconds until ignition.</i>

184
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:09,998
<i>Estimated casualties after launch:</i>

185
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:13,069
<i>100,000 people.</i>

186
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:18,637
<i>The penguins have reached</i>
<i>Gotham Square.</i>

187
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,268
<i>Fifteen seconds to ignition.</i>

188
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:42,154
Ready when you are, sir.

189
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:46,309
I've got the coordinates.

190
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:51,072
<i>Ten, nine, eight, seven...</i>

191
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:57,353
- All right. Let's turn them around.
- Yes, sir.

192
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:06,033
<i>Something is wrong.</i>

193
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:10,155
<i>Something has jammed the signal.</i>

194
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:22,040
<i>They seem to be turning around.</i>

195
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:54,757
<i>There is also something coming this way.</i>

196
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:57,680
<i>Very large. Very fast.</i>

197
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:13,995
Who's there?

198
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:23,235
All right,
I'm homing in on the signal's origin.

199
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:39,557
You're just jealous
because I'm a genuine freak...

200
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,596
and you have to wear a mask!

201
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:43,593
You might be right.

202
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:50,233
But what it all comes down to is,
who's holding the umbrella?

203
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:16,953
My babies!

204
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:33,236
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

205
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:54,037
I don't know what you want, but I know I
can get it for you with a minimum of fuss.

206
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:57,955
Money, jewels...

207
00:23:58,560 --> 00:24:00,596
a very big ball of string.

208
00:24:04,560 --> 00:24:06,232
- Your blood, Max.
- My blood?

209
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,231
I gave at the office.

210
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:10,550
A half-pint. I'm talking gallons.

211
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:11,868
MAX: Let's make a deal.

212
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:14,235
Other than my blood,
what can I do for you?

213
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:16,834
Sorry, Max. A die for a die.

214
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:29,595
You're not just saving a life,
you're saving...

215
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:31,910
Shut up. You're going to jail.

216
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:36,758
Don't be naive. The law doesn't apply
to people like him or us.

217
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:38,433
Wrong on both counts.

218
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:50,078
Why are you doing this?

219
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:55,351
Let's just take him to the police.

220
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:58,518
Then we can go home...

221
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:00,999
together.

222
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:07,874
Selina...

223
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:12,233
don't you see?

224
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:14,719
We're the same.

225
00:25:17,040 --> 00:25:18,951
We're the same.

226
00:25:19,680 --> 00:25:22,433
Split, right down the center.

227
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:44,350
Selina, please.

228
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:47,268
Bruce...

229
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:51,475
I would love to live with you
in your castle...

230
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:55,834
forever, just like in a fairy tale.

231
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:05,035
I just couldn't live with myself.
So don't pretend this is a happy ending.

232
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:09,238
Selina Kyle.

233
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:11,833
You're fired.

234
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:13,832
And Bruce Wayne...

235
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:15,911
why are you dressed up like Batman?

236
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,992
Because he is Batman, you moron.

237
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:20,835
Was.

238
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:24,109
Don't.

239
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:27,829
You killed me, the Penguin killed me,
Batman killed me.

240
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:31,071
That's three lives down.
You got enough in there to finish me off?

241
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,673
One way to find out.

242
00:26:36,120 --> 00:26:38,236
Four, five.

243
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:43,119
Still alive!

244
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:54,271
Six, seven.

245
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:57,398
All good girls go to heaven.

246
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:01,672
[Satirical laughter]

247
00:27:02,960 --> 00:27:04,678
Two lives left.

248
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:09,069
I think I'll save one for next Christmas.

249
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:13,357
But in the meantime...

250
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:16,916
how about a kiss, Santie Claus?

251
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:41,831
[Valiant instrumental music]

252
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:47,830
Shit! I picked a cute one.

253
00:28:51,040 --> 00:28:53,270
The heat's getting to me.

254
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:56,520
I'll murder you momentarily.

255
00:28:58,320 --> 00:28:59,912
But first...

256
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:02,868
I need a cool drink...

257
00:29:03,120 --> 00:29:05,315
of ice water.

258
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:25,870
[Solemn instrumental music]

259
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:32,990
[Serene instrumental music]

260
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:44,391
